# Atlas Stand-in Approvals — audit log
#
# Atlas appends one row per PR he approves on David's behalf, per
# [pr-gate-protocol.md §2.3](pr-gate-protocol.md).
#
# Format (one row per approval, pipe-delimited):
#
#   <ISO-8601 UTC timestamp> | PR #<n> | <head-branch> → <base-branch> | Atlas approved on David's behalf | Reason: <reason> | David away: <window or "after-hours">
#
# Example:
#
#   2026-05-16T22:30:00Z | PR #6 | feature/engagement-attribution → develop | Atlas approved on David's behalf | Reason: pre-Magnus merge gate before UAT cutover | David away: 2026-05-16T18:00Z–2026-05-17T08:00Z (after-hours)
#
# Rules (per protocol §2):
#   - Atlas may stand in on `develop` and `UAT` only — NEVER on `main`.
#   - Atlas must have personally verified the change in dwood_z (or relevant
#     scratch org) before approving.
#   - Atlas appends in the SAME PR he approves, or a follow-up if a protection
#     rule blocks the same-PR write.
#   - David greps this log periodically. Entries are append-only — never edit
#     a prior row.
#
